The paper proposes a method for automated segmentation of brain tumors in MRI images using machine learning techniques such as fully convolutional neural networks and random forests. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis and segmentation. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms such as FCN and random forests suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
